<div class="row">
<div class="col-sm-12 col-xs-12" style="text-align:center; margin-top:50px; margin-bottom:30px;">
<h2 style="font-size:28pt; font-weight:bold; padding-top:35px;">Other key features:</h2>
</div>
</div>
<div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Incremental replication of ESXi, even on ESXi Free hosts and without vCenter</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius Backup is the only software able to perform incremental replications of virtual machines also on ESXi Free hosts (both as source and as target). Iperius performs block-level incremental replication, performing a full replica the first time and then copying only the changes on the disks. Replication is fast, efficient and can take place between any host, without needing to have a vCenter. The replicated machine is immediately bootable in case of need.</p>

</div>
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>"Application consistent" backup on Linux using pre-freeze / post-thaw scripts</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius Backup is able to create "application consistent" backups even of Linux virtual machines, thanks to the automatic execution of file system quiescing scripts (pre-freeze and post-thaw). Quiescing settings can be set individually for each virtual machine and are important for virtual servers that provide database or mail server services, which can have a high file system workload.</p>
</div>
</div>  
<div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Backup of local/networked Hyper-V hosts</h3>
	<p class="text">With only one license, and no need to install any software agents, Iperius can back up unlimited virtual machines from any local or network Hyper-V server. The backup runs quickly and without interruptions, thanks to VSS technology, and you can back up directly to NAS, Tape, or Cloud / FTP. Iperius also supports incremental image backup of virtual machines, with the possibility of truncating application logs.</p>

</div>
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Restore also on different hosts</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius provides powerful features for automatic restores of virtual machines, for ESXi/vCenter as well as Hyper-V. In a few easy steps you can restore a virtual machine, even on different hosts and from specific incremental or differential backups. Restores can also be used to replicate/clone virtual machines on hosts, datasets or different data centres.</p>
</div>
</div>   
       <div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Restore individual files from ESXi VM backups</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius includes a simple and powerful feature to recover single files or folders from the backup of a VMware ESXi virtual machine, without having to restore the entire machine. You can restore files from an incremental or differential backup, then on a specific date, or open a VMDK file to explore its contents and extract the desired files.</p>

</div>
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Restore individual files from Hyper-V VM backups</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius allows you to quickly and easily restore individual files from the backup of a Hyper-V virtual machine. Through a convenient interface it is possible to open VHD or VHDX files (which can be a backup of a VM or an Iperius drive image) and explore its contents, then extract single files or folders with a click.</p>
</div>
</div>   
       <div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>VSphere ESXi Hypervisor Virtualization</h3>
	<p class="text">VMware vSphere, commonly known as "ESXi" from the name of the underlying architecture, is a bare-metal hypervisor, which is installed on the physical server and allows you to manage multiple virtual machines. Iperius can connect to any ESXi server on the network, run the snapshot of the virtual machines and then make hot backups on different devices.</p>

</div>
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Hot backup of ESXi Free</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius can easily run snapshots and hot backups of virtual machines also hosted on ESXi Free. The cost of the virtualization environment and its protection is therefore reduced to only Iperius license, which is perpetual and allows backup of unlimited hosts and virtual machines.</p>
</div>
</div>
       <div class="row">
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Microsoft Hyper-V virtual machines</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius can copy any locked or in-use file, thanks to the Volume Shadow Copy technology. It therefore allows the backup of virtual machines even on Microsoft Hyper-V, without any interruption. The Hyper-V virtualization technology is available on Windows Server 2012, 2008, Server 2016, Server 2019, Windows 10.</p>
</div>                                
<div class="col-lg-6 col-sm-12 col-xs-12">
	<h3>Complete solution for MSPs</h3>
	<p class="text">Iperius is an excellent and profitable solution for companies that provide backup and virtualization services. Thanks to the perpetual license, professional technical support and centralized management through <a href="/web-console-backup.aspx">Iperius Console??</a>, you can easily monitor server and VM backups for all customers. With first-class performance and reliability.</p>
</div> 
